@startuml afls_state_and_speed_to_ahls_glare_cut_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title AFLS State And Speed To AHLS Glare Cut Signal Flow\n(AFLS state + vehicle speed -> AHLS assist/high-beam/glare-cut output)

participant "AFLS state bus" as AFLS #F4F7FB
participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "AHLS\nadaptive headlamp owner" as AHLS #E8F7E8
participant "AHLS state bus" as AhlsBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\nlighting readers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== AHLS Inputs ==

AFLS -> AHLS : frmAflsStateMsg\nAflsMode / BeamPattern / LevelStep
Veh -> AHLS : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngVehicleSpeed
activate AHLS
AHLS -> AHLS : aflsInputStale / vehicleInputStale\nlease checks
AHLS -> AHLS : if stale then clear\nAFLS mode/pattern/level or speed
AHLS -> AHLS : assistState = (AflsMode > 0)
AHLS -> AHLS : highBeamPermit =\n(speed >= 50 and BeamPattern <= 2)
AHLS -> AHLS : glareCutLevel =\n(LevelStep / 2) + 20 when permit == 1
note right of AHLS
Representative gating inputs
- AflsMode
- BeamPattern
- LevelStep
- gVehicleSpeed
end note

== AHLS Publish ==

AHLS -> AhlsBus : frmAhlsStateMsg\nAhlsAssistState / HighBeamPermit / GlareCutLevel
note right of AHLS
Representative outputs
- AhlsAssistState
- HighBeamPermit
- GlareCutLevel
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

AhlsBus -> Obs : adaptive headlamp visibility /\nlighting observers
deactivate AHLS

note over AFLS, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. AFLS state and vehicle speed reach AHLS
2. AHLS applies freshness gates and beam-permit logic
3. AHLS derives final glare-cut level and assist posture
4. AHLS publishes the effective adaptive-headlamp state
end note

@enduml
